# Flatpak apps for the desktop profile (app IDs, one per line).
# Installed by: setup/modules/20-flatpak.sh
# Docs:         docs/setup/flatpak.md, docs/reference/package-managers.md
#
# Only self-contained GUI apps that nothing else needs to invoke by name.
# Anything a script, alias, or xdg-open handler must reach goes in desktop.list
# instead — a flatpak is not on $PATH.
#
# Filesystem overrides (e.g. access to /srv/saito) are NOT applied here; they
# are host-specific and live in 20-flatpak.sh behind a host guard.

# Secrets.
# Flatpak deliberately, despite the sandbox: it tracks upstream far more closely
# (2.7.12 vs 2.7.10 in apt at the time of writing), and the browser extension
# complains when KeePassXC is too old. The sandbox is NOT the thing that breaks
# browser integration — a sandboxed *browser* is. Keep browsers native and this
# works fine, which is how motoko currently runs.
org.keepassxc.KeePassXC

# Image & design
org.gimp.GIMP
com.xnview.XnViewMP
org.darktable.Darktable
org.kde.krita

# AV
# NOTE: mpv is deliberately NOT here — it must be apt. See desktop.list.
org.videolan.VLC
io.github.quodlibet.QuodLibet
io.github.quodlibet.ExFalso

# Social
org.signal.Signal

# Utilities
com.github.tchx84.Flatseal
it.mijorus.gearlever

# Math
io.github.Qalculate
org.speedcrunch.SpeedCrunch

# Notes
md.obsidian.Obsidian

# Browser — ungoogled-chromium only.
# The primary browsers stay native (apt): a sandboxed browser cannot reach
# KeePassXC via native messaging. See docs/setup/browsers.md.
io.github.ungoogled_software.ungoogled_chromium

# Ebooks
# On hold — the ebook reader is not currently in use. Kept here rather than
# deleted so the tool is not forgotten. Uncomment to reinstate.
#com.calibre_ebook.calibre
